value.value: A structural quality of the collection or massing of one physical object within another physical object.
An increased number of physical objects that are accumulated within another physical object usually as a result of a failure to break down or remove objects in a timely manner.
A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing two cusps.
A mobility which is relative high.
A mobility which is relative low.
An elasticity which is relatively high.
An elasticity which is relatively low.
Decreased size or absence of organ, tissue or cell due to a reduction in cell numbers.
A cylindrical shape that is hollow.
A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.
A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of a process that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of a process that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.
A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a consistently sized and approximately round cross-section along its length, which is many times larger than its diameter.

definition.value: Note that a fiber shaped object may take any circuitous or straight path through space (think of a length of string or rope).

value.value:
A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:
1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.
2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.
3. The diagonals bisect each other.
4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.
5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)
6.It possesses rotational symmetry.
7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.
8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.
A shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos2/rt, y = b.cos2/rt
A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.
The temporal relation between the end of the process with respect to a reference process.
The temporal relation between the start of the process with respect to a reference process.
An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.
An angle which is relatively high.
An angle which is relatively low.
Affecting all regions without specificity of distribution.
An affinity inhering in an anatomical structure by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for acidic dyes under specific pH conditions.

definition.value: Eosin stains acidophilic structures, hence eosinophilic is the same as acidophilic.

value.value: Pertaining to the individual parts making up an aggregate fruit like a many-lobed "berry," such as a raspberry.
A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being composed of or possessing inorganic material.
A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of collagen.
A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of swelling or stretching.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel, that are oriented transversely relative to the long axis of the bearer.
A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having one or more nucleus.
A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of keratin.
A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an open, latticed, or porous structure; used especially of bone.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a shape like a ring (a circular shape enclosing a space).
A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.
A quality of a single cell inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

definition.value: Use this term for morphologies that can *only* inhere in a cell, e.g. morphological qualities inhering in a cell by virtue of the presence, location or shape of one or more cell parts.

value.value: A quality inhering in a structure by virtue of it consisting of many of repeated, similar or identical subunits, arranged in some orderly array.

definition.value: A complete coverage of this domain would subclasses homopolymeric, copolymeric, crystalline.

value.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which the bearers stands out or projects beyond a surface or line.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the extent to which the bearer is capable of being stretched or swollen.
Fibrosis is the formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in an organ or tissue in a reparative or reactive process.

definition.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by interruptions or gaps.
This term is intended for use for terms such as MP:0010461 discontinuous pulmonary artery and MP:0004157 interrupted aortic arch.

value.value: A decreased quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decreased magnitude in proportion to the magnitude of another entity.

definition.value: Example: decreased proportion of CD4 T cells relative to total T cells.

value.value: An increased quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's increased magnitude in proportion to the magnitude of another entity.

definition.value: Example: increased proportion of CD4 T cells relative to total T cells.

value.value: A quality inhering in a cell by virtue of the cell having a high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio.

definition.value: A high nuclear/cytolasmic ratio is 70% or higher.

value.value: The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)
A rate of occurrence that is relatively high.
A rate of occurrence that is relatively low.
A cell morphology that inheres in multipolar neurons with densely branched terminal axonal arborizations that form basket-like structures surrounding and synapsing to the somas of target cells.

A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have two principal dendrites that emerge from the soma and begin to branch some distance from it, have few spines, and branch in narrow fields. This is in contrast to bitufted morphology where branching occurs close to the soma.

definition.value: This is specific to cortical bipolar cells and are distinguished from retinal bipolar cell morphology which has an axon and dendrite emerging from opposite ends of the soma.
